"""You can see the description of the task using the code specified in the title on leetcode.
 This program has O(n * log(n)) complexity by time and O(n).

They said to do it without sorting, but the solutions offered three approaches:
1. Sorting (which shouldn't be done)
2. Heaps, which are essentially just heap sort
3. The Quick Select algorithm, which is also essentially sorting...
So I was dissatisfied; they could have simply written "don't use the built-in sort."
"""

class Solution:
    def findKthLargest(self, nums: List[int], k: int) -> int:
        heap =[-elem for elem in nums]
        heapify(heap)
        for i in range(k):
            cur_elem = -heappop(heap)
        return cur_elem
